OL,6,FDuring the trial, Hollick told the
OL,7,Fcourt he had tripped and fallen while
OL,8,Fcarrying Kairo, which may have caused
OL,9,Fhis injuries.
OL,11,FScans showed Kairo was suffering from
OL,12,Fa bleed on the brain and a decision
OL,13,Fwas made to transport him to
OL,14,FBirmingham Children's Hospital, but
OL,15,Fdespite their specialist facilities,
OL,16,Fnothing could be done to save him.
OL,18,FKairo was christened before his life
OL,19,Fsupport was switched off and he died
OL,20,Fin his mother's arms.
